caption: Great family run Nepalese restaurant in Union Square - Himalayan Kitchen was fantastic! We can’t wait to come back. Jay was so friendly and very helpful with menu guidance.  Definitely recommend the spicy chicken momo and the kali mirch ke tikkey kebab plate - the masala sauce was the best I’ve ever had and the chicken is slow roasted and sooo juicy. We got rice pudding to finish it off and can’t wait to come back for more! Go here now.
The food is amazing, they have a great service I have ever seen, the guy in front he was kind and awesome, we got some delicious desserts has incredible flavor.

And the only thing better than the food was how nice Jay was!Make sure to try the rice pudding dessert.  We will be returning, soon!

Really liked this spot!

Never had an issue with the quantity or the quality if you havn't put that together thus far in my review. Its accurately expensive for the Boston area, but underpriced for bougie Somerville. I wont deny the eat in area isn't ideal. Thats why( I hate to do it but..)I have to take a star away. Its very tight and I feel like i'm sitting at the table next to me with strangers while trying to dine. The table ware also doubles as take out containers. I don't mind because it reduces waste and conserves from using excessive water for clean dishes for everyone. Even for you if you don't stuff your face like a chipmunk as I do. They do in the warmer weather offer outdoor seating which is nice. I usually do pick up thought. The service from the man at the register is always on point. He remembers people(not just customers) so well! Greets most by name with a great big smile. Super friendly and great for front of house. The place is always clean when I visit or being cleaned up after a customer leaves. If you do have any kind of complaint or are unsatisfied in any way, I'm sure if you go in and comment about it the next time you visit, they will rectify the situation. This guy seems to genuinely care about the business. I know that because actions speak louder than words. I frequented this pace before Covid shut down the Nation. HK is my among my favorite places in Somerville and I will continue to go there until I move away. Also offers a discount for cash payment

Himalayan Kitchen is hands down the best indian restaurant (+ nepalese, although there are fewer comparisons I'm aware of for that) in Boston, and the only place I regularly get takeout from nowadays. Reasonably priced for takeout (and a steal for lunch specials when available!). The spices they use are a true standout, and they have so many options that range from healthier (aloo bodi tama) to more indulgent (pizzas), all with great taste and the ability to make as spicy as desired. As a vegetarian my top picks would be the spicy momos, paneer chili, shahi paneer masala, aloo gobi, palak paneer, mustard greens, aloo bodi tama. When I'm in the mood for extra spicy things the chyoila (soya chunks) is surprisingly good, chili cheese naan or paratha is a must. Lassis are a generous size, and sweet lassi is a more subtle alternative to mango. The owners are super sweet. I'm really hoping that this restaurant doesn't become a casualty of the current COVID situation, so please visit/takeout and support them :)

I have eaten Indian food all over the country, and I can unequivocally say that the Himalayan Kitchen easily makes the top of my personal list. Their MoMo is delicious, their Naan is just freshly baked buttery goodness, and their curries are fantastic. But what makes the Himalayan Kitchen stand out far above any other place I went to during my tenure in Somerville/Cambridge is the atmosphere in their restaurant. This is a family run business, and they certainly made me feel like family every time I ate there. They remembered my name the second time I dined with them, and it was often a bright spot to go to for a graduate student who didn't really know anyone when I first moved there. The owner was always friendly, and it really meant a lot to me while I was there. I wish I could give this place more stars, as I have not been to any other restaurant that came anywhere close to the warmth I experienced here. The food being some of the best I've ever had just makes this place 6/5. I can't imagine someone coming here and regretting it, and it has my full recommendation!

The restaurant has a fresh and a clean vibe. The guy at the counter was very respectful. Issues with the food though. Choyla: a kind of choyla I have never seen. Very very greasy and lots of spice. Chicken biryani: looked more like rice mixed with chicken curry. Quite greasy for a chicken biryani and too much turmeric. Also I believe raita ( yoghurt and mint sauce) compliments biryani’s way more than plain yoghurt. Momo: was good but the sauce wasn’t enough. I bet this restaurant is cool and awesome; it’s probably one of those days where things didn’t turned out the way it should. I wish them the best and hope the food turns out better next time. Cheers

It's a great local spot. You won't be disappointed!
